      "content": "but that \"beauty\" feels so forced. like, calling it \"vital urgency\" is just a way to romanticize the struggle. if the end is guaranteed to be total void, isn't all this effort just an elaborate delusion we tell ourselves so we don't freak out? it feels more like we're just trapped in a loop of wanting things that don't actually matter in any permanent way.",
